Subject: [PATCH v5 6/7] firmware: arm_ffa: Setup in-kernel users of FFA partitions
Date:   Thu, 25 Mar 2021 14:32:54 +0000
Message-Id: <20210325143255.1532452-7-sudeep.holla@arm.com>
X-Mailer: git-send-email 2.25.1
In-Reply-To: <20210325143255.1532452-1-sudeep.holla@arm.com>
References: <20210325143255.1532452-1-sudeep.holla@arm.com>
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
Precedence: bulk
List-ID: <devicetree.vger.kernel.org>
X-Mailing-List: devicetree@vger.kernel.org

Parse the FFA nodes from the device-tree and register all the partitions
whose services will be used in the kernel.

In order to also enable in-kernel users of FFA interface, let us add
simple set of operations for such devices.

The in-kernel users are registered without the character device interface.

Reviewed-by: Jens Wiklander <jens.wiklander@linaro.org>
Tested-by: Jens Wiklander <jens.wiklander@linaro.org>
Signed-off-by: Sudeep Holla <sudeep.holla@arm.com>
